Package org.apache.http.nio.protocol

Interface HttpAsyncRequestExecutionHandler<T>

  • Type Parameters:
    T - the result type of request execution.
    All Superinterfaces:
    AutoCloseable, Cancellable, Closeable, HttpAsyncRequestProducer, HttpAsyncResponseConsumer<T>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    BasicAsyncRequestExecutionHandler
    @Deprecated
public interface HttpAsyncRequestExecutionHandler<T>
extends HttpAsyncRequestProducer, HttpAsyncResponseConsumer<T>
    Deprecated.
    use HttpAsyncClientExchangeHandler
    HttpAsyncRequestExecutionHandler represents a callback interface that combines functionality of HttpAsyncRequestProducer and HttpAsyncResponseConsumer and is capable of handling logically related series of HTTP request / response exchanges.
    Since:
    4.2
